</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
A genus associated mainly with plants in the family 
<taxonomicName genus="Lamiaceae" lsidName="Lamiaceae" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="genus">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
, but also with plants in the Scrophulariceae, 
<taxonomicName genus="Asteraceae" lsidName="Asteraceae" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="genus">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
and Apicaeae (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
